This document will provide stats and info on personal Spotify extended streaming data which can be downloaded from your Spotify privacy settings by selecting the “Extended streaming history” box and clicking “Request Data”.
Data recorded includes offline data as data is stored in app and uploaded once the device is connected to the internet.

Summary Stats

  • Data in this report is up to 05 May 2024.
  • Listening history on your account dates back to 23 March 2017 with the first song played at 22:45 that day.
  • Over the history of the account:
    • You’ve spent 306,521 minutes (5,109 hours) playing music. That equates to 118 minutes per day, or 8.2% of the time your account has been active!
    • Your most played song is Moving to New York by The Wombats, which has been played 234 times in 7.1 years, or once every 11.1 days.
    • You’ve played songs from 1,774 distinct artists.
    • Your favourite artist is Arctic Monkeys, which you’ve spent 25,787 minutes (430 hours) listening to, across 140 different songs.
    • You’ve played 767 podcast episodes, from 38 different shows. Your most listened to show is JaackMaate’s Happy Hour, with 94 hours listened.
